\cf2 Is mass uploading AI generated ebooks allowed under Google Play Books policies\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Mass uploading AI\uc0\u8209 generated ebooks is not explicitly banned, but it is only allowed if each book complies with Google Play Books\'92 quality, spam, and content policies; otherwise, your catalog or account can be restricted or terminated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 What The Policies Actually Say\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Google\'92s publisher content policies for Play Books prohibit low\uc0\u8209 quality, confusing, or misleading books and metadata, but they do not forbid AI\u8209 generated text as a category.\
\ls7\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Google explicitly focuses on user value, originality, and absence of spam/deception, regardless of whether the content was produced by humans or AI.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 When Mass Uploading Crosses The Line\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'93Unwanted or mass solicitation,\'94 repetitive content, and catalogs that clutter the store with near\uc0\u8209 duplicates or low\u8209 value material are considered spam and can be removed.\
\ls8\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\cf2 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
If many titles share almost identical text, misleading titles/covers, or obvious auto\uc0\u8209 generated junk, Google may treat the operation as deceptive or spammy and act against the account.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 Practical Implication For AI Ebooks\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
