\cf9 \cb11 Is mass uploading AI generated ebooks allowed under Google Play Books policies\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb10 Mass uploading AI\uc0\u8209 generated ebooks is not explicitly banned, but it is only allowed if each book complies with Google Play Books\'92 quality, spam, and content policies; otherwise, your catalog or account can be restricted or terminated.\cb1 \

\fs36 \cb10 What The Policies Actually Say\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls20\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf9 \cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Google\'92s publisher content policies for Play Books prohibit low\uc0\u8209 quality, confusing, or misleading books and metadata, but they do not forbid AI\u8209 generated text as a category.\cb1 \
\ls20\ilvl0\cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Google explicitly focuses on user value, originality, and absence of spam/deception, regardless of whether the content was produced by humans or AI.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf9 \cb10 When Mass Uploading Crosses The Line\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls21\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf9 \cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'93Unwanted or mass solicitation,\'94 repetitive content, and catalogs that clutter the store with near\uc0\u8209 duplicates or low\u8209 value material are considered spam and can be removed.\cb1 \
\ls21\ilvl0\cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
If many titles share almost identical text, misleading titles/covers, or obvious auto\uc0\u8209 generated junk, Google may treat the operation as deceptive or spammy and act against the account.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf9 \cb10 Practical Implication For AI Ebooks\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls22\ilvl0
\fs32 \cf9 \cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Large\uc0\u8209 scale AI catalogs are allowed only if each ebook stands on its own merit: original text, clear structure, accurate metadata, and no policy\u8209 violating content (e.g., explicit, harmful, or fraudulent material).\cb1 \
\ls22\ilvl0\cb10 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Upload volume itself is not the violation; it is mass uploading of repetitive, misleading, or low\uc0\u8209 quality AI books that triggers enforcement under spam and content\u8209 quality rules.\cb1 \
